  "text": "Progression-free survival rates for patients with pituitary tumour have been reported to range from 12 to 69% after surgery, and from 72 to 92% following surgery and radiotherapy [CITATION_1] . These results are based on data collected before GH was added to the replacement therapy regimen for hypopituitarism. While available data on tumour recurrence and regrowth during GH replacement therapy are limited, they are still reassuring.",
